node.text:
“It makes sense that every aspect of a deVOL Kitchen, right down to the handles, should be equally well designed and made. Good design is all about equal consideration for every aspect, form, aesthetic, utility etc. The quality of deVOL is in their attention to detail, the last finishing touches.” - Stephanie O'Leary, deVOL's jeweller and metalsmith. 
#deVOLKitchens

node.title: How we make deVOL handcrafted kitchen handles...

node.text: We did an Instagram story a few months ago now, it was a little behind the scenes look into the @devolceramics studio and a brand new product that we were experimenting with and developing. We always show you the finished products but there's talented people working and being inventive and creative every single day at our Cotes Mill studios, so we love to try and show you as much of the making process as possible. We did a little vote in the story and nearly all of you said you'd like to see these tiles be added as a permanent product to our tile range... so here's a little update! They're not totally ready yet but Hannah is almost there... using our new (but very old!!) tile press and imprinting some of her grandma's vintage lace, she has created the loveliest glossy, Victorian inspired tiles in rich shades of burgundy and blue and pink and brown. As soon as the final tiles are complete and colours and shapes are chosen and they're up on the website we'll let you know, but for now, we hope you enjoy this video of Hannah in action! #deVOLKitchens

node.title: In The Studio: making vintage lace tiles

node.text: Have a little look around @pearllowe's fairytale home and one of our most-loved kitchens ever!! This is eclectic English eccentricity at its very best. A little bit romantic, a little bit edgy and totally unique - we love Pearl's style and feel very lucky to have been able to work with her on this dream of a kitchen. What's your favourite part? #deVOLKitchens

node.text: A little look inside the beautiful Millhouse showrooms with original music, written and performed by Stuart DeRouen.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by deVOL Kitchens in deVOL Kitchens. May be an image of kitchen.

node.text: Bench seats are clever little things. Providing a place to sit, a place to store and in some instances, connecting one run of furniture to another to create a really cohesive design. We designed and made a bench seat for our Loft kitchen at Cotes Mill, from the end of the sink run it turned the corner to meet an elegant Shaker dresser. Topped with a cushion we made from an old grain sack, well, it's one of the best spots to sit in the whole Mill. #deVOLKitchens

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by deVOL Kitchens in Petersham, London. May be an image of furniture and indoor.

node.text: Have you ever seen a cottage kitchen quite like this? It was definitely a first for us. Blending industrial and country styles and that bold wash of deep Pantry Blue... wow. Forget twee, country kitchens can be dark and cosy, dramatic and simple, unique and traditional, all at the same time. #deVOLKitchens

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by deVOL Kitchens in New Jersey with @nicole_franzen, and @and.studio.interiors. May be an image of kitchen.

node.text:
What better way to start the week than with a brand new totally gorgeous kitchen photo. This space belongs to one of our very cool customers across the pond in New Jersey and when she sent us a few shots of the finished room, well, you can see why we fell in love. A  beautiful big brownstone with tall ceilings and wooden floors and airy rooms, a perfect home for our handcrafted deVOL cupboards, lights and stools... oh how we'd like to be perching up on that island with our morning coffee.

Thank you so much to @and.studio.interiors and @nicole_franzen for the photos, we are head over heels in love with this kitchen. #deVOLKitchens

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by deVOL Kitchens in Devol Kitchens - The New York Showroom. May be an image of furniture and indoor.

node.text: Our Haberdasher's furniture is the perfect antidote to minimalism, it is so full of character and almost seems to have its own personality. These pieces of furniture can shape a room and make a home. #deVOLKitchens

node.text: Oh my goodness we really do love an open and closed pantry shot, but this time it’s a Sub-Zero fridge duo!! wow - only a teeny bit jealous of this tremendously stocked refrigerator, it looks incredible, it looks delicious and it looks so neat. #deVOLKitchens

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by deVOL Kitchens in deVOL Kitchens. May be an image of kitchen.

node.text: Thank you, thank you, thank you!! For all the love and support and beautiful messages and words of kindness on our TV show so far. It's scary stuff, putting yourself out there for millions of people to see and comment on but we're proud of what we do here at deVOL and think our little world is a pretty unique and special one and it seems you think so too. Well, that means so much to us. New episodes will be out once a week now and oh boy, the next one is a gooden. #deVOLKitchens

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by deVOL Kitchens on August 06, 2021 tagging @houseofhackney, @joannagaines, @magnolia, @chipgaines, @hapdesigns, @devolpaul, @discoveryplus, @magnolianetwork, and @discoveryplusuk. May be an image of furniture and indoor.

node.text:
In ‘A Kitchen Fit for a Castle’ we hang out with the wonderful Frieda and Javvy of iconic British design house @houseofhackney in their Cornish castle!! Designing a deVOL kitchen for a castle was an exciting and truly unique experience for us all, a little daunting too but it really had to be something memorable and we think Frieda and Javvy's idea of adding a little something extra to our deVOL cupboards made them totally castle-worthy and took this room to the next level... we won't give too much away because this place and the way in which Frieda and Javvy have transformed it is breathtaking, it’s a fantasy world, a wonderland, the stuff dreams are made of, a magical place that just has to be seen to be believed. 

‘For the Love of Kitchens’ is now available on @magnolianetwork via the discovery+ app. Happy Friday everybody! #deVOLKitchens #HouseofHackney #ForTheLoveOfKitchens #MagnoliaNetwork

node.text:
The deVOL TV Show is finally here... well just about!! The first two episodes of 'For the Love of Kitchens' will be premiering tomorrow 6th August on @magnolianetwork on @discoveryplus and @discoveryplusUK so all our wonderful friends and followers in the US and UK can watch!! We're nervous and excited and proud and scared and ahhh well we suppose you'll all just have to let us know what you think now!! We can't wait to share everything deVOL with you all. A glimpse into the everyday lives of our carpenters, artisan makers, designers, the people behind deVOL and where it all started. Join our customers too, on their kitchen journeys and see their projects unfold before your eyes. A unique series that is full of beautiful things and passionate people. The episodes will be available both in the US and the UK via the discovery+ app and we've written a handy guide on the deVOL Journal for anyone who'd like to know how to watch, just follow the link in our bio.

Oh we really do hope you're going to love it, swipe left for a little taste of what's to come... #deVOLKitchens #ForTheLoveOfKitchens #MagnoliaNetwork

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by deVOL Kitchens in Hertfordshire. May be an image of furniture and kitchen.

node.text: What a kitchen. South facing with oodles of space, lofty ceilings, doors straight out to a very private garden and a few Shaker cupboards, it sounds pretty idyllic to us. How lovely would it be to know you are only ever a few steps away from a little veg patch with fresh produce you've grown yourself, or a bed of beautiful blooms just waiting to fill those gorgeous glass vintage demijohn bottles in the corner. #deVOLKitchens

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by deVOL Kitchens in Devol Kitchens - St. John's Square Showroom. May be an image of indoor.

node.text: The cupboard doors would never be closed with an interior as beautiful as this. Hardwood shelving fixed at just the right height, spice racks and internal drawers decorated with pretty cardframe pulls, solid tongue and groove backboards, a little traditional brass pantry vent and a lick of Clerkenwell Blue all over. #deVOLKitchens

location.name: Devol Kitchens - St. John's Square Showroom
